The game is a bore reliever, greatly thanks to the new PvP system but needs 
some optimization to maintain this game's exciting features such as new 
Chapters in Campaign

Good: + different characters to choose from + a lot of upgrades for your 
character + graphics are minimalistic + tons of game modes + the campaign 
dungeons are offline (and the game itself too) + game is good for people 
who like minimalistic graphics, side scrolling action rpgs, and grinding + 
addicting to some + you can get gems by playing but... Bad: - gem rewards 
are few and getting them would be grindy. People who don't play the game 
much might think its too repetitive - please add more heroes in hero 
dungeons - most grammar is a bit off and hard to understand the game 
sometimes - hero information is lacking, theres no stats displayed until 
you get them. This is just for the sake of comparison for getting and 
considering new characters. Skills are not labled or named also. - the 
characters reminds me from a different game.... - as other people said, 
some rewards and purchases don't work. - no jump option. That means you 
cant avoid those cannons. - please make the save files transferable to 
other devices (does it mean the saves are not transferable to other mobile 
platforms or saves are non-transferable when you get a new phone. Maybe the 
grammar is just the problem here) - characters are expensive - some hero 
descriptions look cut and incomplete The only difference between the free 
version and the paid version of this game is you have two characters 
(prince and monkey) that are unobtainable in the free version. Monkey is 
free (0 gems) in the paid version though... the rest is just the same. 
Misc: ‚Ä¢ no story in the game but who cares ;) ‚Ä¢ i just hope you improve 
what I said above as well as the other people saying. Also an item lock 
option would be nice so you won't accidentally sell good items

content: Damn! It is my first time purchasing an app using my card....

I personally liked the game. It's something of a hack and slash, which I've been looking for a while now. You spend the game mostly fighting monsterd in the campaign mode, since it's the easiest way to make coins.  For all you new players, be ready to either grind or line up your credit cards, because most, if not everything is purchasable with real money.  The characters are fun to use and it's fun finding which character suits your fighting style, offering a wide variety of characters to grind for or to throw your credit card at.  To be honest with you, I should bored with this, but there's something about that just makes me come back. You do the same thing over and over again, but it's always different in a way.  My complaint comes with the PVP. It's a good idea, it really is, but it just doesn't do it for me. Often that not people decide to leave the match causing a "dogfall"? I think it's something like that. Just a small suggestion, punish players for leaving a PVP match. Take away a bit of coins or something. I know it sounds a bit heartless but this will stop players from quitting on you in the middle of a fight.  With that said, the game is fun. New updates come out often which improves the game and the team is quite active.  Thanks for wasting my time in a good way.
